ACID ARROW

Usage       : cast 'acid arrow' <victim>

By means of this spell, an acidic arrow is shot forth from the casters
hand. The acid splatters against the victim causing them harm.
#
FLY

Usage       : cast 'fly' <victim>

This spell casuses the victim's feet to rise up off the ground and and fly
in any direction.
#
SLEEP

Usage       : cast 'sleep' <victim>

The casting of this spell causes the victim to fall asleep rendering them
prone for attacks.
#
BARKSKIN

Usage       : cast 'barkskin' <victim>

This spell causes the victims skin to become bark for a few hours, causing
the victim to become harder to hit.
#
STONESKIN

Usage       : cast 'stoneskin' <victim>

This spell causes the victim's skin to become stone for a few hours,
causing the victim to become harder to hit.
#
TELEPORT

Usage       : cast 'teleport' <victim>

This spell allws the caster to travel great distances with only the use of
words. The caster will teleport to the victims name choosen.
#
WEAKNESS

Usage       : cast 'weakness' <victim>

The use of this spell causes the victim to be sapped of strength making
him weaker, and less of a threat.
#
ARMOR

Usage       : cast 'armor' [target]

By means of this spell the cleric creates a magical field of force
that serves as a suit of armor that protects the wearer. This spell
has no additional affects to those already armored with the spell.

See also: AC
#
BLESS

Usage       : cast 'bless' <victim | object>

Upon uttering the spells spell the victim becomes more accurate in
melee combat and posses a slightly better resistant to spells being
casted upon them.

Bless on an item currently has no defined action.  It is only possible
to bless non-evil items, and the object blessed may weigh no more
than five pounds per level of caster. 
#
BLINDNESS

Usage       : cast 'blindness' <victim>

The blindess spell will blind its victim who fails their saving throw.
Not only will it cause them to become blind, but will also raise their
armor class making them easier targets.

See also: AC
#
"BURNING HANDS"

Usage       : cast 'burning hands' <victim>

When the wizard casts this spells, a jet of searing flame shoots from
his fingertips. The flame shoots out causing harm to the victim.

See also: "CHILL TOUCH"
#
CAST

Usage: cast <spell> [target]

For "magical" people.  If you want to throw a spell at someone or something.

Example:

  > cast burning-hands dog

  Note that spells with multiple words must have the words seperated by a
dash.  The first space after the spell name begins (in this case, dog) is
for the targets - some spells will require multiple arguments.

See also: help on each individual spell:

Examples:

  > help spell cure light
  > help spell ventri
  > help spell energy drain
#
"CHARM PERSON"

Usage       : cast 'charm person' <victim>

It is not possible to charm anyone that is already charmed.
A charmed person will follow you, and not be able to attack you, you
can order the charmed person using the order command.

Ordering a charmed person to quit the game is against the rules. If this
happens the person will be punished.

See also: FOLLOW, ORDER
#
"CHILL TOUCH"

Usage       : cast 'chill touch' <victim>

When the caster completes thi spell, a blue glow encompasses his hand.
This energy attacks the life force of any living creature upon which the
wizard scores a successful attack.

See also: "MAGIC MISSILE"
#
COLORSPRAY "COLOR SPRAY"

Usage       : cast 'color spray' <victim>

The wizard causes a vivid, fan-shap of clashing colors to spring forth
from his hand.

For help on actual color, see:  ANSI
#
"CREATE FOOD"

Usage       : cast 'create food'

This spell instantly creates a fresh piece of bread.

See also: "CREATE WATER"
#
"CREATE WATER"

Usage       : cast 'create water' <drink container>

The caster stares at the container and says the magic words. If successful
a liquid will form inside the container.

See also: "CREATE FOOD"
#
"CURE BLIND"

Usage       : cast 'cure blind' <victim>

This spell will cure a person blinded by the "blindness" spell.
#
"CURE CRITIC"

Usage       : cast 'cure critic' <victim>

This spell cures gashes and large wounds.
#
"CURE LIGHT"

Usage       : cast 'cure light' <victim>

Cures minor wounds and scratches.
#
CURSE

Usage       : cast 'curse' <victim | object>

Curse cast on a person will reduce thier ability to attack
When cast upon an object, the object will become undropable.
#
"DETECT ALIGNMENT"

Usage       : cast 'detect alignment'


Allows the caster to detect the nature of those around them.


See also: "DETECT INVISIBILITY"
#
"DETECT INVISIBILITY"

Usage       : cast 'detect invisibility' [self]

This spell enables you to see invisible items and people.
#
"DETECT MAGIC"

Usage       : cast 'detect magic' [self]

This spell will let you see the magical aura surrounding magical
objects.
#
"DETECT POISON"

Usage       : cast 'detect poison' <victim | food | drink>

Cast on food or drinks (drink containers) you will be able to
sense if it is poisoned.

Cast on a person you will be able to see if that person is
poisoned.
#
"DISPEL EVIL"

Usage       : cast 'dispel evil' <victim>

This spell will only affect evil creatures. If successful, this spell
will cause a great amount of pain to the person its being casted upon.

See also: DISPEL GOOD
#
"DISPEL GOOD"

Usage       : cast 'dispel good' <victim>

This spell will only affect good creatures. If successful, this spell
will cause a great amount of pain to the person its being cast upon.

See also: DISPEL EVIL
#
EARTHQUAKE

Usage       : cast 'earthquake'
When uttering the words to this spell, the caster causing the ground to
open up which cases all those around him to fall.
#
"ENCHANT WEAPON"

Usage       : cast 'enchant weapon' <weapon>

This spell will enchant normal wapons, making them more powerful than
others.
#
"ENERGY DRAIN"

Usage       : cast 'energy drain' <victim>

When cast upon its victim, the energy absorbs the life from within,
giving the caster of the spell a partial benefit of the drain.
#
FIREBALL

Usage       : cast 'fireball' <victim>

When cast, a giant ball of fire shoots from the casters hand, causing the
vitim an intense amount of pain, if not death.
#
HARM

Usage       : cast 'harm' <victim>

By means of this spell the caster lunges forward and grabs the victim. The
spells causes so much pain to the victim it can almost kill the victim out
right.
#
HEAL

Usage       : cast 'heal' <victim>

This spell heals the wounds that are which almost fatal to the victim.
#
INFRAVISION

Usage       : cast 'infravision'

Allows the caster to detect the heat given off by objects giving them
the ability to have much better vision in dark conditions.

